Let's not forget the Hungarian Revolution back in the 50's! I got to watch it when I was a dependent service brat in Wiesbaden, Germany. We sat around waiting for the evacuation order as the spy planes screamed their takeoff from the main runway. That's about all we did for that event.<br><br>
The Vietnam War, like all these other altercations, was a civil war, only perhaps more convoluted than other civil actions. Now, there is no big brother left to intervene should internal forces in Vietnam decide that they are fed up with the present worker's paradise.<br><br>
There are those who feel that we can kill it off with money and cheap sneaker factories, and diplomatic exhortations of human rights. I don't think so. There was a terrible human price that got us where we are at today, and there will be more when the pendulum starts to swing back in another 20 years or so.<br><br>
Depressing, isn't it, when you realize you are living through the old adage of history repeating itself!<br><br>

